/* ** If the argument is a codepoint corresponding to a lowercase letter ** in the ASCII range with a diacritic added, return the codepoint ** of the ASCII letter only. For example, if passed 235 - "LATIN ** SMALL LETTER E WITH DIAERESIS" - return 65 ("LATIN SMALL LETTER ** E"). The resuls of passing a codepoint that corresponds to an ** uppercase letter are undefined. */
/* ** Return true if the argument interpreted as a unicode codepoint ** is a diacritical modifier character. */

function.name: sqlite3Fts5UnicodeIsdiacritic

unit.comment: /* ** Interpret the argument as a unicode codepoint. If the codepoint ** is an upper case character that has a lower case equivalent, ** return the codepoint corresponding to the lower case version. ** Otherwise, return a copy of the argument. ** ** The results are undefined if the value passed to this function ** is less than zero. */

function.name: sqlite3Fts5UnicodeCatParse
